meta_keywords: Special Purpose Marine Air Ground Task Force Combat Camera
data.meta_description: U.S. Marine Corps Capt. Learlin J. Lejeune III, assistant operations officer, Special Purpose Marine Air Ground Task Force - Crisis Response - Central Command 16.2, provides an interview regarding a Mission Rehearsal Exercise at a base in southern Jordan, Sept. 13, 2016. The MRX is a collective training event where the MAGTF elements collaborate to refine individual and cooperative capabilities. SPMAGTF - CR - CC is a self-sustaining expeditionary unit, designed to provide a broad range of crisis response capabilities throughout the Central Command area of responsibility, using organic aviation, logistical, and ground combat assets, to include embassy reinforcement and tactical recovery of aircraft and personnel. (U.S. Marine Corps video by Cpl. Chelsey K. Courtney)
